Some users from one of our customers have trouble to change the color of their team calendars.

After some analysis I discovered, that the REST endpoint color.json returns the following JSON:

{code}
{"success":false,"fieldErrors":[{"field":"spaceKeyAutocomplete","errorMessages":["Ungültiges Leerzeichen"]}]}
{code}

The users had no space configured. After I added a space to their calendars I could change to color.

I'm not sure why they had no color. I can imagine two possible scenarios.

1. the space was no required field in an older version of team calendars!?!
2. the space the users configured for their calendar was renamed oder removed.

*The major problem is that to user gets no information, why his attempts to change to color fail.*

